description: The center of Egypt’s capital erupted in violence again on Friday as military police beat up demonstrators challenging military rule.
title: Military Police Clash With Protesters in Cairo
title_page: Military Police Clash With Protesters in Cairo - The New York Times
maintext:
Slide 1 of 8,
Egyptian military police clashed with protesters challenging military rule in Cairo on Friday. The chaos came after Egypt’s first parliamentary elections since the ouster 10 months ago of former strongman Hosni Mubarak.
